    "Title": "ANSA-2024:0584: qemu security update (Moderate)",
    "Affected": {
      "Family": "unix",
      "Platform": [
        "Anolis OS 23"
      ]
    },
    "References": [
      {
        "RefID": "ANSA-2024:0584",
        "RefURL": "https://anas.openanolis.cn/errata/detail/ANSA-2024:0584",
        "Source": "ANSA"
      }
    ],
    "Description": "Package updates are available for Anolis 23 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\n\nCVE-2024-3446:\nA double free vulnerability was found in QEMU virtio devices (virtio-gpu, virtio-serial-bus, virtio-crypto), where the mem_reentrancy_guard flag insufficiently protects against DMA reentrancy issues. This issue could allow a malicious privileged guest user to crash the QEMU process on the host, resulting in a denial of service or allow arbitrary code execution within the context of the QEMU process on the host.",
    "Advisory": {
      "Severity": "Moderate",
      "Issued": {
        "Date": "2024-07-08"
      },
      "Updated": {
        "Date": "2024-07-08"
      },
      "Cves": [
